Ugly Movement 
When I get “ugly” it’s a FEELING. I will never stop embracing my ugly, eccentric, outlandish weird self. it is WHO I AM. Dance is my passion, therapy and it has saved me in ways I can’t even comprehend. It’s how I express myself.  To my students, thank you for being inspirations to me. I will never stop for you and everyone who feels voiceless in scenarios when they just wanna express who they are. UGLY & EXPRESSIVE MOVEMENT FOR LIFE!!!!!!!!!!!! Dancing with my ride or dies to my favorite artist evaaa @teamseshbones🩻🩻TEE shirts made by me & Choreography by me!!👽
I feel more empowered every night. Thank you @tarinadoolittle for capturing us on tour. 🖤 Salt Lake City tonight!

it’s a feeling I can’t remember………………..

It takes bravery to tap into this in front of others. And you all did. IM SO PROUD OF YOU 🥹 Last round Wednesday 4:30-6PM 👽 @brickhouse.nyc #uglymovement

Pain Sybarite 23’

My first sybarite and not even a year into this journey in NYC. This piece was entirely about feeling. My cast (family) spent alot of time together, not to make this piece the most clean perfect piece, but to connect emotionally. To understand each others message. It was an emotional rollercoaster putting this piece together. It forced me to face my own personal pains in order for my cast to gracefully embrace theirs.  A sacred experience we all experienced together. As a unit. Turning pain into power. 

A special thank you @joedilegge_ for being the most amazing sounding board throughout this. You gave me space to feel safe to share visions day in day out. You helped me bring this to life. And that bone breaking…All HIM. Brilliance. 

This is our family’s vision. I hope you felt it. Thank you @sybariteproductions for having us🖤 Ugly Movement forever

A packed house Wednesday night for The FIRST EVER Ugly Movement show debuted at @saintvitusbar! Putting an entire show together from scratch in 3 weeks as a one woman business was NO JOKE.  I am eternally grateful 🖤🔪 I truly can’t believe a year into this journey in NYC has lead me here. 

Thank you to my beautiful cast, for the support you carried along this creative crunch time. For lending a hand when needed and dedicating yourselves to this vision. 

Thank you to every single person who came to the show. I’m blown away and touched with the amount of people that support this movement. It is my baby and I will never stop giving a platform for artists to be FREE.. thank you to all that stayed and watched the story unfold throughout the show. Thank you for an unbelievable amount of outpouring love and messages. It’s just the beginning baby! Thank you for having us @saintvitusbar @confinesworld 

A special Shoutout to @cecil23_ for helping with lighting and being the best right hand man! thank you @megananna_g and @lycanzero_ for your beautiful cameos! 🖤
